U.S. Buyout




Filippo Passerini is an Operating Executive focused on U.S. buyout opportunities.
Previously, Mr. Passerini was Group President Global Business Services at Procter & Gamble and Chief Information Officer. Mr. Passerini joined Procter & Gamble in 1981, and for more than three decades helped to build businesses in developed and developing markets. He has lived and worked in the U.K., Latin America, Greece, Italy, Turkey and the U.S.
Mr. Passerini is a Director of the Boards of Directors of United Rentals and Carlyle portfolio company ProKarma Holdings Inc.
He received a doctorate in statistics and operations research from the University of Rome.



























 




